'''肖恩·迈克尔·斯派塞'''（{{lang-en|'''Sean Michael Spicer'''}}，<ref name="nytimes2004">{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2004/11/14/fashion/weddings/rebecca-miller-sean-spicer.html?_r=0 |title=Fashion Weddings: Rebecca Miller & Sean Spicer |work=The New York Times |date=November 14, 2004 |accessdate=November 11, 2016 |archivedate=2017年2月6日 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6o4yp2s9h?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2004/11/14/fashion/weddings/rebecca-miller-sean-spicer.html?_r=1 |dead-url=no |quote=Mr. Spicer, also 33... |df= }}</ref><ref name="newport">{{Cite news|title=Born|date=September 25, 1971|newspaper=[[The_Newport_Daily_News|The Newport Daily News]]|location=Newport County, Rhode Island|page=2|quote=Spicer – Sept. 23, 1971, at North Shore Hospital in Manhasset, Long Island, a son to Mr. and Mrs. Michael Spicer (Kathryn Grossman)...}}</ref>{{bd|1971年|9月23日}}），美國政治人物，在[[唐納·川普|川普]][[美國總統|總統]]時期擔任[[白宫新闻秘书|白宫新闻秘书]]，兼任{{tsl|en|White House Communications Director|白宮通訊聯絡辦公室主任|白宮通訊聯絡主任}}。2011年至2017年間，史派瑟曾任[[共和黨全國委員會|共和黨全國委員會]]通訊總監，並於2015年至2017年間兼任共和黨首席戰略家。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=285878558&privcapId=4272999&previousCapId=4272999&previousTitle=Republican%20National%20Committee%20Inc|title=Sean Spicer: Executive Profile and Biography|publisher=[[Bloomberg_L.P.|Bloomberg]]|accessdate=January 3, 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161111190949/http://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=285878558&privcapId=4272999&previousCapId=4272999&previousTitle=Republican%20National%20Committee%20Inc|archivedate=November 11, 2016|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在擔任白宮新聞秘書期間，史派瑟曾做出許多具有爭議或謬誤的言論<ref name="KesslerJan22">{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/fact-checker/wp/2017/01/22/spicer-earns-four-pinocchios-for-a-series-of-false-claims-on-inauguration-crowd-size |title=Spicer earns Four Pinocchios for false claims on inauguration crowd size |work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]] |access-date=January 23, 2017 |first=Glenn |last=Kessler |author-link=Glenn Kessler (journalist) |date=January 22, 2017 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170122194054/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/fact-checker/wp/2017/01/22/spicer-earns-four-pinocchios-for-a-series-of-false-claims-on-inauguration-crowd-size/ |archivedate=January 22, 2017 |df=|quote=He managed to make a series of false and misleading claims in service of a relatively minor issue....Spicer earns Four Pinocchios, but seriously, we wish we could give five.}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Danny Vinik|work=Politico|date=January 24, 2017|url=http://www.politico.com/blogs/donald-trump-administration/2017/01/spicer-trump-voter-fraud-claim-234121|title=Spicer makes misleading voter fraud claim to defend Trump's false voter fraud claim|quote=Pressed for those studies, Spicer then offered a falsehood of his own}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Aaron Blake|work=Washington Post|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2017/04/18/the-white-houses-misleading-statements-about-trumps-armada-heading-to-north-korea/|title=The White House's misleading statements about Trump's 'armada' heading to North Korea|date=April 18, 2017|accessdate=2017-08-01|archive-date=2018-07-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180710164023/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2017/04/18/the-white-houses-misleading-statements-about-trumps-armada-heading-to-north-korea/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，與白宮記者團關係一度緊張。<ref name="CillizzaConference">{{cite news|author=Chris Cillizza|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2017/03/17/sean-spicers-thursday-press-conference-was-a-new-low-for-the-trump-white-hous/|date=March 17, 2017|title=Sean Spicer's Thursday news conference was a new low for the Trump White House|work=Washington Post|quote=Spicer has had a contentious relationship with the media since his first appearance on the podium|accessdate=2017-08-01|archive-date=2018-07-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180710164630/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2017/03/17/sean-spicers-thursday-press-conference-was-a-new-low-for-the-trump-white-hous/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="JohnsonResigns">{{cite news|author=Ted Johnson|url=http://variety.com/2017/biz/news/sean-spicer-resigns-white-house-press-secretary-1202502307/|work=Variety|title=Sean Spicer Resigns as White House Press Secretary|quote=Spicer had been with the administration from the start, but almost immediately had a contentious relationship with the media.|date=July 21, 2017}}</ref><ref name="LiptakReporting">{{cite news|author=Kevin Liptak|title=Reality Check: Sean Spicer hits the media over crowds|publisher=CNN|date=January 21, 2017|url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/01/21/politics/sean-spicer-fact-check/index.html|quote=Spicer launched into a tirade against the media Saturday, slamming what he said was unfair reporting of the attendance of President Donald Trump's inauguration, along with other criticisms. Many of the facts he cited, however, are inaccurate.}}</ref>例如：史派瑟曾再三強調[[2017年美國總統就職典禮|川普總統的就職典禮]]是歷任以來最盛大的，而媒體故意低估觀禮人數<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vanityfair.com/news/2017/03/sean-spicer-withdraw-press-briefings|title=Sean Spicer's Agony Will Never End—to His Boss's Delight|first=Tina|last=Nguyen|magazine=[[Vanity_Fair_(magazine)|Vanity Fair]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/03/31/business/media/april-ryan-white-house-spicer-trump.html|title=For April Ryan, Clashes With the White House Bring a New Kind of Prominence|first=Michael M.|last=Grynbaum|date=March 31, 2017|newspaper=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170402011036/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/03/31/business/media/april-ryan-white-house-spicer-trump.html|archivedate=April 2, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/02/15/politics/sean-spicer-white-house/index.html|title=Sean Spicer isn't finished|first=Dylan|last=Byers|publisher=[[CNN|CNN]]|department=Politics|access-date=May 19, 2017|date=February 15, 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170512161626/http://www.cnn.com/2017/02/15/politics/sean-spicer-white-house/index.html|archivedate=May 12, 2017}}</ref>；此言論受到嚴厲批評後，[[美國總統顧問|總統顧問]][[凱莉安·康威|凱莉安·康威]]表示史派瑟有關就職典禮觀禮人數的陳述是所謂「[[另類事實|另類事實]]」。<ref name="independent">{{cite news|last1=Benwell|first1=Max|title=White House press conference: When is it, how can I watch it, and what will Sean Spicer say?|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/donald-trump-press-conference-when-is-it-how-can-i-watch-sean-spicer-alternative-facts-a7541806.html|work=[[The_Independent|The Independent]]|date=January 23, 2017|accessdate=January 23, 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202065004/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/donald-trump-press-conference-when-is-it-how-can-i-watch-sean-spicer-alternative-facts-a7541806.html|archivedate=February 2, 2017}}</ref>

2017年7月21日，史派瑟自行宣布辭去白宮新聞秘書一職。<ref name = resignCBS>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/sean-spicer-resigns-as-white-house-press-secretary-report/|title=Sean Spicer resigns as White House press secretary|publisher=CBS News|date=July 21, 2017|accessdate=2017-08-01|archive-date=2018-02-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180220001340/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/sean-spicer-resigns-as-white-house-press-secretary-report/|dead-url=no}}</ref>據了解，他強烈不同意特朗普任命沒有相關經驗的[[安東尼·斯卡拉姆齊|安東尼·斯卡拉姆齊]]為白宮通訊聯絡主任。<ref name = Thrush>Glenn Thrush (July 21, 2017). [https://www.nytimes.com/2017/07/21/us/politics/sean-spicer-resigns-as-white-house-press-secretary.html Sean Spicer Resigns as White House Press Secretary] {{Wayback|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/07/21/us/politics/sean-spicer-resigns-as-white-house-press-secretary.html |date=20170721160008 }}. ''The New York Times''.</ref>

== 私人生活 ==
2004年11月13日，史派瑟在華盛頓哥倫比亞特區的{{tsl|en|St. Alban's Episcopal Church (Washington, D.C.)|聖奧本主教堂}}迎娶了時任電視製作人麗貝卡·米勒。<ref name="nytimes2004"/>婚後倆人同住於維吉尼亞州的[[亚历山德里亚_(弗吉尼亚州)|亞歷山卓]]，並育有兩子。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/style/what-happens-when-you-tie-your-career-to-donald-trump-ask-sean-spicer-in-a-few-months/2016/08/16/c492be3a-5f4f-11e6-8e45-477372e89d78_story.html |title=What happens when you tie your career to Donald Trump? Ask Sean Spicer in a few months. |last=Terris |first=Ben |date=August 16, 2016 |last2=Terris |first2=Ben |newspaper=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]] |accessdate=January 31, 2017 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170126071111/https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/style/what-happens-when-you-tie-your-career-to-donald-trump-ask-sean-spicer-in-a-few-months/2016/08/16/c492be3a-5f4f-11e6-8e45-477372e89d78_story.html |archivedate=January 26, 2017 |df= }}</ref>麗貝卡·米勒是{{tsl|en|National Beer Wholesalers Association|美國啤酒批發商協會}}的資深副總裁，專責通訊與公共事務。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cosmopolitan.com/politics/a8531830/sean-spencer-white-house-press-secretary |title=Who Is Sean Spicer? 10 Things to Know About Trump's Pick for Press Secretary |first=Kayleigh |last=Roberts |work=[[Cosmopolitan_(magazine)|Cosmopolitan]] |date=January 22, 2017 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170129010031/http://www.cosmopolitan.com/politics/a8531830/sean-spencer-white-house-press-secretary/ |archivedate=January 29, 2017 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbwa.org/content/rebecca-spicer|publisher=[[National_Beer_Wholesalers_Association|National Beer Wholesalers Association]]|title=Rebecca Spicer|accessdate=February 7, 2016|archive-date=February 2, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202020419/https://www.nbwa.org/content/rebecca-spicer|dead-url=no}}</ref>此外，史派瑟是一名天主教徒。<ref>{{cite news|author1=J.A.|title=Donald Trump’s spokesman quits|url=https://www.economist.com/blogs/democracyinamerica/2017/07/tragic-tale-spicey-0|accessdate=July 24, 2017|work=[[The_Economist|The Economist]]|date=July 22, 2017}}</ref>

